article.description: Conference player of the year Kevin Hervey scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead top seed UT Arlington to a 74-51 victory over No. 8 seed Coastal Carolina on Friday in the Sun Belt Tou
article.headline: Hervey leads top seed UTA into Sun Belt semifinals
article.linkText: Hervey leads top seed UTA into Sun Belt semifinals
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- Conference player of the year Kevin Hervey scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to lead top seed UT Arlington to a 74-51 victory over No. 8 seed Coastal Carolina on Friday in the Sun Belt Tournament quarterfinals. The Mavericks (25-7) will play No. 4 seed Texas State, a 63-51 winner over Louisiana-Monroe earlier Friday, in a Saturday semifinal. Jorge Bilbao added 14 points and 10 rebounds and Jalen Jones 12 points. Jaylen Shaw scored 14 points and Artur Labinowicz 12 for the Chanticleers (16-17). An 8-0 run gave UTA the lead for good late in the first half and the Mavericks led 29-27 at the break. Hervey strung together all three of his 3-pointers to give the Mavericks a 57-44 lead with four minutes remaining with UTA pulling away in the final 2 1/2 minutes by scoring 15 straight points, 11 on free throws. The teams split their regular-season matchups.
